gland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Alice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Alice had at least 1 daughter with Robert Clifton. She died after 1442."},"et":{"–after 1442":"–pärast 1442","–1447":"–1447","1412–1456":"1412–1456","–1442":"–1442","1447":"1447","1412":"1412","1456":"1456","1442":"1442","after 1442":"pärast 1442","Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, England"},"fi":{"–after 1442":"–1442 jälkeen","–1447":"–1447","1412–1456":"1412–1456","–1442":"–1442","1447":"1447","1412":"1412","1456":"1456","1442":"1442","after 1442":"1442 jälkeen","Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, England"},"fr":{"–after 1442":"–après 1442","–1447":"–1447","1412–1456":"1412–1456","–1442":"–1442","1447":"1447","1412":"1412","1456":"1456","1442":"1442","after 1442":"après 1442","Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Alice a eu au moins 1 fille avec Robert Clifton. Elle est décédée après 1442."},"de":{"–after 1442":"–nach 1442","–1447":"–1447","1412–1456":"1412–1456","–1442":"–1442","1447":"1447","1412":"1412","1456":"1456","1442":"1442","after 1442":"nach 1442","Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, England","lifeSummary":"Alice hatte mit Robert Clifton mindestens 1 Tochter. Sie starb nach 1442."},"